race.comment: THREE TEES (3) didn't manage the wide gate here last time in a strong form race, but was good prior, beaten a nose. Draws a bit better today and has a handy 2kg claim. Has a key gear addition and gets his chance. CASH PIT (1) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest here when he found one too good over 1400. He led in that and is nicely placed to give this a shake. BONEWOOD (6) was safely held here on debut, starting a short-priced favourite. Didn't have the best of it and expect him to make quick improvement up in trip for the top stable. INTREPID LAD (2) has switched yards and will race over further. Will probably need it, but Butler sticks from a solid trial and that interest.
